\f3\fs34 \cf2 Removing the mask substantially improves both MA (+0.215) and SP (+0.014). The copy mask was intended to enforce meaning preservation by restricting generation to source vocabulary, but instead caused destructive early termination: the mask narrows the output distribution to source words, while the repetition penalty simultaneously penalises tokens already generated, leaving the end-of-sequence token as the highest-scoring option after just 2\'963 words. Masked outputs degraded into fragments such as 
\f5\fs28\fsmilli14450 \cb4 "the as a"
\f3\fs34 \cb1  and 
\f5\fs28\fsmilli14450 \cb4 "and by hath\'94
\f3\fs34 \cb1 ,  formally compliant with the mask but semantically empty. This is a concrete instance of the constraint interaction failure mode identified by Belouadi & Eger (2023): independently sensible decoding constraints can compose destructively. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl612\qc\partightenfactor0
